<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR COMPRESSOR: HOLSET SS 296 AND QE 296/338 - REASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Assembly of the allowable repair components and parts requires a small torque wrench with a range of
                100 to 400 in-lbs. (11.3 to 45.2 N&#8226;m) or 5 to 40 ft-lbs. (6.8 to 54.2 N&#8226;m), anti-seize
                compound or a Teflon based lubricant, a clean work area and good mechanical know-how.
            </para>
            <para>If the cylinder head has been removed from the compressor, always install a new head gasket on a
                clean, nick and burr free crankcase.
            </para>
            <para>Gasket sealing surfaces must be clean and free of all old gasket material, carbon, rust, etc. Surfaces
                must be free of scratches, gouges, burrs, etc. After assuring all gasket surfaces are clean and free of
                the above, inspect the head and cover for flatness. Use a flat plate and feeler gauges.
            </para>
            <para>Cylinder heads must be flat within .001 inch (.03 mm) between any two adjacent bolt holes. Cylinder
                top cover must be flat within .0025 inch (.06 mm) between any two adjacent bolt holes and .004 inch (.10
                mm) total.
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="10">
            <title>SS 296 COMPRESSOR</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install wear plate into cylinder head (
                    <hotlnk document="s04014_8.xml" xrefid="f0401435">Figure 35</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install exhaust valve spring (
                    <hotlnk document="s04014_8.xml" xrefid="f0401434">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>It is recommended that new springs be installed during cylinder head rebuild.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install exhaust valve (
                    <hotlnk document="s04014_8.xml" xrefid="f0401433">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>It is recommended that new exhaust valves be installed during Maintenance or Service.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new, red O-ring seal on the exhaust valve seat (
                    <hotlnk document="s04014_8.xml" xrefid="f0401432">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <para>Lubricate the O-ring after assembly. Also lubricate the exhaust valve seat surface in the head for
                    ease of assembly into the head. Use clean SAE 15W40 engine oil. Some models have an O-ring in the
                    head to seal the exhaust seat stem. If there is an O-ring groove in the head near the exhaust seat
                    stem, be sure to install a new O-ring from the Maintenance or Service Kit.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a hand press and an air compressor seat installation tool (ZTSE-4364) to press the
                    exhaust valve seat into the head (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401464">Figure 64</hotlnk>). If an arbor is not available, an arbor made with
                    1.500 inch (38 mm) diameter stock, a flat and perpendicular bottom with a .045 inch (1.1 mm) chamfer
                    to clear seat may be used.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401464" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401464" filename="../figg04/G0401464.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 64. Press Exhaust Valve Seat Into Head</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Excessive force on the exhaust valve seat can distort the sealing lips and result in
                            exhaust valve leakage.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new head gasket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401465">Figure 65</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401465" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401465" filename="../figg04/G0401465.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 65. Head Gasket</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the head (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401466">Figure 66</hotlnk>). Be sure the assembly marks made during disassembly
                    are lined up.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401466" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401466" filename="../figg04/G0401466.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 66. Install Head</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new cover gasket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401467">Figure 67</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401467" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401467" filename="../figg04/G0401467.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 67. Cover Gasket</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401468">Figure 68</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401468" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401468" filename="../figg04/G0401468.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 68. Install Cover</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the four flat washers, lock- washers and head bolts (
                    <hotlnk document="s04014_8.xml" xrefid="f0401428">Figure 28</hotlnk>). Lubricate the head bolt
                    threads and under head with clean engine oil, SAE 15W40, before installation. Make certain that the
                    head gasket holes are in good alignment with the head and crankcase holes to prevent damage to the
                    head gasket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the head bolts in the following
                    <hotlnk xrefid="hl0401403">torquing sequence</hotlnk>
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401469">Figure 69</hotlnk>):
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401469" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401469" filename="../figg04/G0401469.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 69. Tightening Sequence</caption>
                </figure>
                <table id="hl0401403">
                    <title>Torquing Sequence Table</title>
                    <tgroup cols="3">
                        <colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.50in"/>
                        <colspec colname="2" colwidth="1.50in"/>
                        <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.50in"/>
                        <thead>
                            <row rowsep="0">
                                <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                    <para>Step</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="2" align="center">
                                    <para>
                                        <emph type="bold">Ft-lbs.</emph>
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="3" align="center">
                                    <para>(N&#8226;m)</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row rowsep="0">
                                <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                    <para>1</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="2" align="center">
                                    <para>5</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="3" align="center">
                                    <para>(7)</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row rowsep="0">
                                <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                    <para>2</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="2" align="center">
                                    <para>10</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="3" align="center">
                                    <para>(14)_</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row rowsep="0">
                                <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                    <para>3</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="2" align="center">
                                    <para>15</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="3" align="center">
                                    <para>(20)</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row rowsep="0">
                                <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                    <para>4</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="2" align="center">
                                    <para>20</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="3" align="center">
                                    <para>(28)</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>It is recommended that no external or extra chassis or engine brackets be installed on the
                            air compressor head bolts. However, if necessary, assure that adequate thread engagement
                            exists after the added bracket is installed and the bolt affected must be tightened to 20
                            ft-lbs. (28 N&#8226;m).
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the intake valve spring with
                    <emph type="bold">tang end down</emph>
                    (
                    <hotlnk document="s04014_8.xml" xrefid="f0401426">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>It is recommended that a new spring be installed during Maintenance or Service.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the intake valve (
                    <hotlnk document="s04014_8.xml" xrefid="f0401425">Figure 25</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>It is recommended that a new intake valve be installed during Maintenance or Service.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the intake valve seat with the flange side up (
                    <hotlnk document="s04014_8.xml" xrefid="f0401424">Figure 24</hotlnk>). The 3-leg intake valve seat
                    has an open top with 3 slots for unloader cap alignment.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new unloader vee seal into the unloader body (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401470">Figure 70</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401470" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401470" filename="../figg04/G0401470.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 70. Unloader Vee Seal</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The seal must be installed with the grooved side up. Lubricate the unloader valve bore
                            above and below the unloader vee seal liberally with high temperature grease (Accro Lube
                            Teflon grease or equivalent)
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new O-ring seal on the unloader valve body (
                    <hotlnk document="s04014_8.xml" xrefid="f0401422">Figure 22</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use clean SAE 15W40 oil to lubricate O-ring seal, or use Accro Lube Teflon grease or
                    equivalent (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401471">Figure 71</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401471" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401471" filename="../figg04/G0401471.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 71. Lubricate O-Ring Seal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the unloader spring into the intake valve seat. Liberally lube the unloader
                    valve body bore and unloader cap with high temperature grease (Accro Lube Teflon grease or
                    equivalent). Install the unloader cap into the intake valve seat. The 3 legs of the unloader cap
                    must align with the 3 slots in the intake valve seat (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401472">Figure 72</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401472" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401472" filename="../figg04/G0401472.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 72. Align 3 Legs With Slots</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the unloader valve body over the unloader cap and spring. Hold down the unloader
                    valve body and install the washers and bolts. Use new washers in kits. Lubricate the unloader valve
                    body bolt threads and under the bolt head with clean engine oil (SAE 15W40) before installation.
                    Tighten to 10 ft-lbs. (14 N&#8226;m) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401473">Figure 73</hotlnk>). The two unloader valve body bolts must not be used to
                    attach any brackets.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401473" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401473" filename="../figg04/G0401473.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 73. Tighten Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>The unloader valve body bolts must not be tightened before the head bolts. Failure to
                            follow this procedure will cause damage to the unloader valve body and top cover and result
                            in early failure.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
